-- McGraw-Hill quarterly profit, revenue rise
-- 
-- Tue Apr 24, 2007 7:28am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/24/us-mcgrawhill-results-idUSWEN685720070424

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Publisher McGraw-Hill Cos. Inc. MHP.N reported a higher quarterly profit on Tuesday, helped by strong performance at its Standard & Poor's unit. 

 The company, which also owns BusinessWeek magazine, said first-quarter net income rose to $143.8 million, or 40 cents a share, from $74.2 million, or 20 cents a share, a year ago. Revenue rose nearly 14 percent to $1.3 billion.